SIMPLE: underneath
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underneath
<hw>Un`der*neath"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>undirnepe</ets>. See <er>Under</er>, and <er>Beneath</er>.]</ety>
<def>Beneath; below; in a lower place; under; <as>as, a channel
<ex>underneath</ex> the soil</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or sullen mole, that runneth <qex>underneath</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underneath</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Underneath
<hw>Un`der*neath"</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>Under; beneath;
below.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Underneath</qex> this stone lie⟦br⟧
As much beauty as could die.</q> <rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underniceness</ent>⟦br⟧
